sm:flex-row sm:items-center gap-2 sm:gap-4 mb-3 justify-between"><h1 class="text-2xl font-semibold font-header">Structured Outputs</h1><div class="flex items-center border rounded-md w-fit" data-ignore-md="true"><button class="inline-flex items-center justify-center whitespace-nowrap font-medium ring-offset-background transition-colors focus-visible:outline-none aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="24" height="24" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" class="lucide lucide-chevron-down h-4 w-4" aria-hidden="true"><path d="m6 9 6 6 6-6"></path></svg></button></div></div>
<p class="text-sm my-3">Guarantee model responses strictly conform to your JSON schema for reliable, type-safe data structures.</p>
<h2 id="introduction" class="[&amp;:not(:first-child)]:mt-12 mb-3 text-xl w-fit font-semibold font-header hover:underline"><a href="#introduction" class="anchor-link">Introduction</a></h2>
<p class="text-sm my-3">Structured Outputs is a feature that makes your model responses strictly conform to your provided <a class="inline-flex items-center gap-1 transition-colors duration-200 font-inter text-foreground underline underline-offset-2 hover:text-primaryaccent text-sm" href="https://json-schema.org/overview/what-is-jsonschema">JSON Schema</a> or throws an error if the model cannot produce a compliant response. The endpoint provides customers with the ability to obtain reliable data structures.</p>
<br/>
<p class="text-sm my-3">This feature&#x27;s performance is dependent on the model&#x27;s ability to produce a valid answer that matches your schema. If the model fails to generate a conforming response, the endpoint will return an error rather than an invalid or incomplete result.</p>
<br/>
<p class="text-sm my-3">Key benefits:</p>
<ol class="list-decimal my-2 text-sm">
<li class="ml-6 my-1.5 text-sm"><strong>Binary output:</strong> Either returns valid JSON Schema-compliant output or throws an error</li>
<li class="ml-6 my-1.5 text-sm"><strong>Type-safe responses:</strong> No need to validate or retry malformed outputs</li>
<li class="ml-6 my-1.5 text-sm"><strong>Programmatic refusal detection:</strong> Detect safety-based model refusals programmatically</li>
<li class="ml-6 my-1.5 text-sm"><strong>Simplified prompting:</strong> No complex prompts needed for consistent formatting</li>
</ol>
<br/>
<p class="text-sm my-3">In addition to supporting Structured Outputs in our API, our SDKs also enable you to easily define your schemas with <a class="inline-flex items-center gap-1 transition-colors duration-200 font-inter text-foreground underline underline-offset-2 hover:text-primaryaccent text-sm" href="https://docs.pydantic.dev/latest/">Pydantic</a> and <a class="inline-flex items-center gap-1 transition-colors duration-200 font-inter text-foreground underline underline-offset-2 hover:text-primaryaccent text-sm" href="https://zod.dev/">Zod</a> to ensure further type safety. The examples below show how to extract structured information from unstructured text.</p>
<h2 id="supported-models" class="[&amp;:not(:first-child)]:mt-12 mb-3 text-xl w-fit font-semibold font-header hover:underline"><a href="#supported-models" class="anchor-link">Supported models</a></h2>
<p class="text-sm my-3">Structured Outputs is available with the following models:</p>

<p class="text-sm my-3">For all other models, you can use <a class="inline-flex items-center gap-1 transition-colors duration-200 font-inter text-foreground underline underline-offset-2 hover:text-primaryaccent text-sm" href="#json-object-mode">JSON Object Mode</a> to get a valid JSON object, though it may not match your schema.</p>
<br/>
<p class="text-sm my-3"><strong>Note:</strong> <a class="inline-flex items-center gap-1 transition-colors duration-200 font-inter text-foreground underline underline-offset-2 hover:text-primaryaccent text-sm" href="/docs/text-chat#streaming-a-chat-completion">streaming</a> and <a class="inline-flex items-center gap-1 transition-colors duration-200 font-inter text-foreground underline underline-offset-2 hover:text-primaryaccent text-sm" href="/docs/tool-use">tool use</a> are not currently supported with Structured Outputs.</p>

from pydantic import BaseModel
from typing import Literal
import json

client = Groq()

class ProductReview(BaseModel):
product_name: str
rating: float
sentiment: Literal[&quot;positive&quot;, &quot;negative&quot;, &quot;neutral&quot;]
key_features: list[str]

response = client.chat.completions.create(
model=&quot;moonshotai/kimi-k2-instruct-0905&quot;,
messages=[
{&quot;role&quot;: &quot;system&quot;, &quot;content&quot;: &quot;Extract product review information from the text.&quot;},
{
&quot;role&quot;: &quot;user&quot;,
&quot;content&quot;: &quot;I bought the UltraSound Headphones last week and I&#x27;m really impressed! The noise cancellation is amazing and the battery lasts all day. Sound quality is crisp and clear. I&#x27;d give it 4.5 out of 5 stars.&quot;,
},
],
response_format={
&quot;type&quot;: &quot;json_schema&quot;,
&quot;json_schema&quot;: {
&quot;name&quot;: &quot;product_review&quot;,
&quot;schema&quot;: ProductReview.model_json_schema()
}
}
)

review = ProductReview.model_validate(json.loads(response.choices[0].message.content))
print(json.dumps(review.model_dump(), indent=2))</code></pre></div><div class="hidden"><pre class="overflow-auto text-sm p-4"><code>curl https://api.groq.com/openai/v1/chat/completions \

<h3 id="structured-outputs-vs-json-mode" class="mt-8 mb-3 text-base w-fit font-semibold font-header hover:underline"><a href="#structured-outputs-vs-json-mode" class="anchor-link">Structured Outputs vs JSON mode</a></h3>
<p class="text-sm my-3">Structured Outputs builds on <a class="inline-flex items-center gap-1 transition-colors duration-200 font-inter text-foreground underline underline-offset-2 hover:text-primaryaccent text-sm" href="#json-object-mode">JSON Object Mode</a> with enhanced capabilities. Both produce valid JSON, but Structured Outputs goes further by matching your response to your schema exactly or throws an error if the model cannot produce a conforming response.</p>
<br/>
<p class="text-sm my-3"><strong>Note:</strong> Constrained decoding (which is designed to output JSON Schema compliance without errors) is currently only available on a limited-access Llama 3.1 8B model. For all other models, the endpoint attempts validation that may return errors if the model cannot produce a conforming response.</p>
<br/>
<p class="text-sm my-3">We recommend using Structured Outputs instead of JSON Object Mode whenever possible.</p>
<h2 id="examples" class="[&amp;:not(:first-child)]:mt-12 mb-3 text-xl w-fit font-semibold font-header hover:underline"><a href="#examples" class="anchor-link">Examples</a></h2>

from pydantic import BaseModel
import json

client = Groq()

class ValidationStatus(BaseModel):
is_valid: bool
syntax_errors: list[str]

class SQLQueryGeneration(BaseModel):
query: str
query_type: str
tables_used: list[str]
estimated_complexity: str
execution_notes: list[str]
validation_status: ValidationStatus

response = client.chat.completions.create(
model=&quot;moonshotai/kimi-k2-instruct-0905&quot;,
messages=[
{
&quot;role&quot;: &quot;system&quot;,
&quot;content&quot;: &quot;You are a SQL expert. Generate structured SQL queries from natural language descriptions with proper syntax validation and metadata.&quot;,
},
{&quot;role&quot;: &quot;user&quot;, &quot;content&quot;: &quot;Find all customers who made orders over $500 in the last 30 days, show their name, email, and total order amount&quot;},
],
response_format={
&quot;type&quot;: &quot;json_schema&quot;,
&quot;json_schema&quot;: {
&quot;name&quot;: &quot;sql_query_generation&quot;,
&quot;schema&quot;: SQLQueryGeneration.model_json_schema()
}
}
)

sql_query_generation = SQLQueryGeneration.model_validate(json.loads(response.choices[0].message.content))
print(json.dumps(sql_query_generation.model_dump(), indent=2))</code></pre></div><div class="hidden"><pre class="overflow-auto text-sm p-4"><code>curl https://api.groq.com/openai/v1/chat/completions \

from pydantic import BaseModel
import json

client = Groq()

class KeyEntity(BaseModel):
entity: str
type: str

class EmailClassification(BaseModel):
category: str
priority: str
confidence_score: float
sentiment: str
key_entities: list[KeyEntity]
suggested_actions: list[str]
requires_immediate_attention: bool
estimated_response_time: str

response = client.chat.completions.create(
model=&quot;moonshotai/kimi-k2-instruct-0905&quot;,
messages=[
{
&quot;role&quot;: &quot;system&quot;,
&quot;content&quot;: &quot;You are an email classification expert. Classify emails into structured categories with confidence scores, priority levels, and suggested actions.&quot;,
},
{&quot;role&quot;: &quot;user&quot;, &quot;content&quot;: &quot;Subject: URGENT: Server downtime affecting production\\n\\nHi Team,\\n\\nOur main production server went down at 2:30 PM EST. Customer-facing services are currently unavailable. We need immediate action to restore services. Please join the emergency call.\\n\\nBest regards,\\nDevOps Team&quot;},
],
response_format={
&quot;type&quot;: &quot;json_schema&quot;,
&quot;json_schema&quot;: {
&quot;name&quot;: &quot;email_classification&quot;,
&quot;schema&quot;: EmailClassification.model_json_schema()
}
}
)

email_classification = EmailClassification.model_validate(json.loads(response.choices[0].message.content))
print(json.dumps(email_classification.model_dump(), indent=2))</code></pre></div><div class="hidden"><pre class="overflow-auto text-sm p-4"><code>curl https://api.groq.com/openai/v1/chat/completions \

<span></span><span class="token" style="color:#569CD6">const</span><span> result </span><span class="token" style="color:#d4d4d4">=</span><span> </span><span class="token known-class-name" style="color:#4ec9b0">JSON</span><span class="token" style="color:#d4d4d4">.</span><span class="token method property-access" style="color:#dcdcaa">parse</span><span class="token" style="color:#d4d4d4">(</span><span>response</span><span class="token" style="color:#d4d4d4">.</span><span class="token property-access">choices</span><span class="token" style="color:#d4d4d4">[</span><span class="token" style="color:#b5cea8">0</span><span class="token" style="color:#d4d4d4">]</span><span class="token" style="color:#d4d4d4">.</span><span class="token property-access">message</span><span class="token" style="color:#d4d4d4">.</span><span class="token property-access">content</span><span> </span><span class="token" style="color:#d4d4d4">||</span><span> </span><span class="token" style="color:#ce9178">&quot;{}&quot;</span><span class="token" style="color:#d4d4d4">)</span><span class="token" style="color:#d4d4d4">;</span><span>
</span><span></span><span class="token" style="color:#4ec9b0">console</span><span class="token" style="color:#d4d4d4">.</span><span class="token method property-access" style="color:#dcdcaa">log</span><span class="token" style="color:#d4d4d4">(</span><span>result</span><span class="token" style="color:#d4d4d4">)</span><span class="token" style="color:#d4d4d4">;</span></code></pre></div><div class="hidden"><pre class="overflow-auto text-sm p-4"><code>from groq import Groq
from pydantic import BaseModel
import json

client = Groq()

class ValidationResult(BaseModel):
is_valid: bool
status_code: int
error_count: int

class FieldValidation(BaseModel):
field_name: str
field_type: str
is_valid: bool
error_message: str
expected_format: str

class ComplianceCheck(BaseModel):
follows_rest_standards: bool
has_proper_error_handling: bool
includes_metadata: bool

class Metadata(BaseModel):
timestamp: str
request_id: str
version: str

class StandardizedResponse(BaseModel):
success: bool
data: dict
errors: list[str]
metadata: Metadata

class APIResponseValidation(BaseModel):
validation_result: ValidationResult
field_validations: list[FieldValidation]
data_quality_score: float
suggested_fixes: list[str]
compliance_check: ComplianceCheck
standardized_response: StandardizedResponse

response = client.chat.completions.create(
model=&quot;moonshotai/kimi-k2-instruct-0905&quot;,
messages=[
{
&quot;role&quot;: &quot;system&quot;,
&quot;content&quot;: &quot;You are an API response validation expert. Validate and structure API responses with error handling, status codes, and standardized data formats for reliable integration.&quot;,
},
{&quot;role&quot;: &quot;user&quot;, &quot;content&quot;: &quot;Validate this API response: {\&quot;user_id\&quot;: \&quot;12345\&quot;, \&quot;email\&quot;: \&quot;invalid-email\&quot;, \&quot;created_at\&quot;: \&quot;2024-01-15T10:30:00Z\&quot;, \&quot;status\&quot;: \&quot;active\&quot;, \&quot;profile\&quot;: {\&quot;name\&quot;: \&quot;John Doe\&quot;, \&quot;age\&quot;: 25}}&quot;},
],
response_format={
&quot;type&quot;: &quot;json_schema&quot;,
&quot;json_schema&quot;: {
&quot;name&quot;: &quot;api_response_validation&quot;,
&quot;schema&quot;: APIResponseValidation.model_json_schema()
}
}
)

api_response_validation = APIResponseValidation.model_validate(json.loads(response.choices[0].message.content))
print(json.dumps(api_response_validation.model_dump(), indent=2))</code></pre></div><div class="hidden"><pre class="overflow-auto text-sm p-4"><code>curl https://api.groq.com/openai/v1/chat/completions \

<h2 id="schema-validation-libraries" class="[&amp;:not(:first-child)]:mt-12 mb-3 text-xl w-fit font-semibold font-header hover:underline"><a href="#schema-validation-libraries" class="anchor-link">Schema Validation Libraries</a></h2>
<p class="text-sm my-3">When working with Structured Outputs, you can use popular schema validation libraries like <a class="inline-flex items-center gap-1 transition-colors duration-200 font-inter text-foreground underline underline-offset-2 hover:text-primaryaccent text-sm" href="https://zod.dev/">Zod</a> for TypeScript and <a class="inline-flex items-center gap-1 transition-colors duration-200 font-inter text-foreground underline underline-offset-2 hover:text-primaryaccent text-sm" href="https://docs.pydantic.dev/latest/">Pydantic</a> for Python. These libraries provide type safety, runtime validation, and seamless integration with JSON Schema generation.</p>
<h3 id="support-ticket-classification" class="mt-8 mb-3 text-base w-fit font-semibold font-header hover:underline"><a href="#support-ticket-classification" class="anchor-link">Support Ticket Classification</a></h3>
<p class="text-sm my-3">This example demonstrates how to classify customer support tickets using structured schemas with both Zod and Pydantic, ensuring consistent categorization and routing.</p>
<div class="w-full"><div dir="ltr" data-orientation="horizontal"><div class="w-full overflow-x-auto overflow-y-hidden"><div role="tablist" aria-orientation="horizontal" class="flex h-10 gap-6 font-header font-normal text-sm text-foreground" tabindex="-1" data-orientation="horizontal" style="outline:none"><button type="button" role="tab" aria-selected="true" <h2 id="implementation-guide" class="[&amp;:not(:first-child)]:mt-12 mb-3 text-xl w-fit font-semibold font-header hover:underline"><a href="#implementation-guide" class="anchor-link">Implementation Guide</a></h2>
<h3 id="schema-definition" class="mt-8 mb-3 text-base w-fit font-semibold font-header hover:underline"><a href="#schema-definition" class="anchor-link">Schema Definition</a></h3>
<p class="text-sm my-3">Design your JSON Schema to constrain model responses. Reference the <a class="inline-flex items-center gap-1 transition-colors duration-200 font-inter text-foreground underline underline-offset-2 hover:text-primaryaccent text-sm" href="#examples">examples</a> above and see <a class="inline-flex items-center gap-1 transition-colors duration-200 font-inter text-foreground underline underline-offset-2 hover:text-primaryaccent text-sm" href="#schema-requirements">supported schema features</a> for technical limitations.</p>
<br/>
<p class="text-sm my-3"><strong>Schema optimization tips:</strong></p>
<ul class="list-disc my-1 text-sm">
<li class="ml-6 my-1.5 text-sm">Use descriptive property names and clear descriptions for complex fields</li>
<li class="ml-6 my-1.5 text-sm">Create evaluation sets to test schema effectiveness</li>
<li class="ml-6 my-1.5 text-sm">Include titles for important structural elements</li>
</ul>
<h3 id="api-integration" class="mt-8 mb-3 text-base w-fit font-semibold font-header hover:underline"><a href="#api-integration" class="anchor-link">API Integration</a></h3>
<p class="text-sm my-3">Include the schema in your API request using the <code class="bg-gray-100 dark:bg-gray-800 py-0.5 px-[0.5em] rounded-[4px]">response_format</code> parameter:</p>

const response = await groq.chat.completions.create({
model: &quot;moonshotai/kimi-k2-instruct-0905&quot;,
messages: [
{ role: &quot;system&quot;, content: &quot;You are a helpful math tutor. Guide the user through the solution step by step.&quot; },
{ role: &quot;user&quot;, content: &quot;how can I solve 8x + 7 = -23&quot; }
],
response_format: {
type: &quot;json_schema&quot;,
json_schema: {
name: &quot;math_response&quot;,
schema: {
type: &quot;object&quot;,
properties: {
steps: {
type: &quot;array&quot;,
items: {
type: &quot;object&quot;,
properties: {
explanation: { type: &quot;string&quot; },
output: { type: &quot;string&quot; }
},
required: [&quot;explanation&quot;, &quot;output&quot;],
additionalProperties: false
}
},
final_answer: { type: &quot;string&quot; }
},
required: [&quot;steps&quot;, &quot;final_answer&quot;],
additionalProperties: false
}
}
}
});

const result = JSON.parse(response.choices[0].message.content || &quot;{}&quot;);
console.log(result);</code></pre></div><div class="hidden"><pre class="overflow-auto text-sm p-4"><code>curl https://api.groq.com/openai/v1/chat/completions \
-H &quot;Authorization: Bearer $GROQ_API_KEY&quot; \
-H &quot;Content-Type: application/json&quot; \
-d &#x27;{
&quot;model&quot;: &quot;moonshotai/kimi-k2-instruct-0905&quot;,
&quot;messages&quot;: [
{
&quot;role&quot;: &quot;system&quot;,
&quot;content&quot;: &quot;You are a helpful math tutor. Guide the user through the solution step by step.&quot;
},
{
&quot;role&quot;: &quot;user&quot;,
&quot;content&quot;: &quot;how can I solve 8x + 7 = -23&quot;
}
],
&quot;response_format&quot;: {
&quot;type&quot;: &quot;json_schema&quot;,
&quot;json_schema&quot;: {
&quot;name&quot;: &quot;math_response&quot;,
&quot;schema&quot;: {
&quot;type&quot;: &quot;object&quot;,
&quot;properties&quot;: {
&quot;steps&quot;: {
&quot;type&quot;: &quot;array&quot;,
&quot;items&quot;: {
&quot;type&quot;: &quot;object&quot;,
&quot;properties&quot;: {
&quot;explanation&quot;: { &quot;type&quot;: &quot;string&quot; },
&quot;output&quot;: { &quot;type&quot;: &quot;string&quot; }
},
&quot;required&quot;: [&quot;explanation&quot;, &quot;output&quot;],
&quot;additionalProperties&quot;: false
}
},
&quot;final_answer&quot;: { &quot;type&quot;: &quot;string&quot; }
},
&quot;required&quot;: [&quot;steps&quot;, &quot;final_answer&quot;],
&quot;additionalProperties&quot;: false
}
}
}
}&#x27;</code></pre></div></div></div>
<h3 id="error-handling" class="mt-8 mb-3 text-base w-fit font-semibold font-header hover:underline"><a href="#error-handling" class="anchor-link">Error Handling</a></h3>
<p class="text-sm my-3">Schema validation failures return HTTP 400 errors with the message <code class="bg-gray-100 dark:bg-gray-800 py-0.5 px-[0.5em] rounded-[4px]">Generated JSON does not match the expected schema. Please adjust your prompt.</code></p>
<br/>
<p class="text-sm my-3"><strong>Resolution strategies:</strong></p>
<ul class="list-disc my-1 text-sm">
<li class="ml-6 my-1.5 text-sm">Retry requests for transient failures</li>
<li class="ml-6 my-1.5 text-sm">Refine prompts for recurring schema mismatches</li>
<li class="ml-6 my-1.5 text-sm">Simplify complex schemas if validation consistently fails</li>
</ul>
<h3 id="best-practices" class="mt-8 mb-3 text-base w-fit font-semibold font-header hover:underline"><a href="#best-practices" class="anchor-link">Best Practices</a></h3>
<p class="text-sm my-3"><strong>User input handling:</strong> Include explicit instructions for invalid or incompatible inputs. Models attempt schema adherence even with unrelated data, potentially causing hallucinations. Specify fallback responses (empty fields, error messages) for incompatible inputs.</p>
<br/>
<p class="text-sm my-3"><strong>Output quality:</strong> Structured outputs are designed to output schema compliance but not semantic accuracy. For persistent errors, refine instructions, add system message examples, or decompose complex tasks. See the <a class="inline-flex items-center gap-1 transition-colors duration-200 font-inter text-foreground underline underline-offset-2 hover:text-primaryaccent text-sm" href="/docs/prompting">prompt engineering guide</a> for optimization techniques.</p>
<h2 id="schema-requirements" class="[&amp;:not(:first-child)]:mt-12 mb-3 text-xl w-fit font-semibold font-header hover:underline"><a href="#schema-requirements" class="anchor-link">Schema Requirements</a></h2>
<p class="text-sm my-3">Structured Outputs supports a <a class="inline-flex items-center gap-1 transition-colors duration-200 font-inter text-foreground underline underline-offset-2 hover:text-primaryaccent text-sm" href="https://json-schema.org/docs">JSON Schema</a> subset with specific constraints for performance and reliability.</p>
<h3 id="supported-data-types" class="mt-8 mb-3 text-base w-fit font-semibold font-header hover:underline"><a href="#supported-data-types" class="anchor-link">Supported Data Types</a></h3>
<ul class="list-disc my-1 text-sm">
<li class="ml-6 my-1.5 text-sm"><strong>Primitives:</strong> String, Number, Boolean, Integer</li>
<li class="ml-6 my-1.5 text-sm"><strong>Complex:</strong> Object, Array, Enum</li>
<li class="ml-6 my-1.5 text-sm"><strong>Composition:</strong> anyOf (union types)</li>
</ul>
<h3 id="mandatory-constraints" class="mt-8 mb-3 text-base w-fit font-semibold font-header hover:underline"><a href="#mandatory-constraints" class="anchor-link">Mandatory Constraints</a></h3>
<p class="text-sm my-3"><strong>Required fields:</strong> All schema properties must be marked as <code class="bg-gray-100 dark:bg-gray-800 py-0.5 px-[0.5em] rounded-[4px]">required</code>. Optional fields are not supported.</p>
<br/>

<p class="text-sm my-3"><strong>Closed objects:</strong> All objects must set <code class="bg-gray-100 dark:bg-gray-800 py-0.5 px-[0.5em] rounded-[4px]">additionalProperties: false</code> to prevent undefined properties. This ensures strict schema adherence.</p>

<p class="text-sm my-3"><strong>Union types:</strong> Each schema within <code class="bg-gray-100 dark:bg-gray-800 py-0.5 px-[0.5em] rounded-[4px]">anyOf</code> must comply with all subset restrictions:</p>
<br/>

</span><span> </span><span class="token" style="color:#9cdcfe">&quot;type&quot;</span><span class="token" style="color:#d4d4d4">:</span><span> </span><span class="token" style="color:#ce9178">&quot;object&quot;</span><span class="token" style="color:#d4d4d4">,</span><span>
</span><span> </span><span class="token" style="color:#9cdcfe">&quot;properties&quot;</span><span class="token" style="color:#d4d4d4">:</span><span> </span><span class="token" style="color:#d4d4d4">{</span><span>
</span><span> </span><span class="token" style="color:#9cdcfe">&quot;payment_method&quot;</span><span class="token" style="color:#d4d4d4">:</span><span> </span><span class="token" style="color:#d4d4d4">{</span><span>
</span><span> </span><span class="token" style="color:#9cdcfe">&quot;anyOf&quot;</span><span class="token" style="color:#d4d4d4">:</span><span> </span><span class="token" style="color:#d4d4d4">[</span><span>
</span><span> </span><span class="token" style="color:#d4d4d4">{</span><span>

<br/>
<p class="text-sm my-3"><strong>Root recursion:</strong> Use <code class="bg-gray-100 dark:bg-gray-800 py-0.5 px-[0.5em] rounded-[4px]">#</code> to reference the root schema:</p>
<br/>

</span><span> </span><span class="token" style="color:#9cdcfe">&quot;type&quot;</span><span class="token" style="color:#d4d4d4">:</span><span> </span><span class="token" style="color:#ce9178">&quot;array&quot;</span><span class="token" style="color:#d4d4d4">,</span><span>
</span><span> </span><span class="token" style="color:#9cdcfe">&quot;items&quot;</span><span class="token" style="color:#d4d4d4">:</span><span> </span><span class="token" style="color:#d4d4d4">{</span><span>
</span><span> </span><span class="token" style="color:#9cdcfe">&quot;$ref&quot;</span><span class="token" style="color:#d4d4d4">:</span><span> </span><span class="token" style="color:#ce9178">&quot;#/$defs/file_node&quot;</span><span>
</span><span> </span><span class="token" style="color:#d4d4d4">}</span><span>
</span><span> </span><span class="token" style="color:#d4d4d4">}</span><span class="token" style="color:#d4d4d4">,</span><span>
</span><span> </span><span class="token" style="color:#d4d4d4">{</span><span>
</span><span> </span><span class="token" style="color:#9cdcfe">&quot;type&quot;</span><span class="token" style="color:#d4d4d4">:</span><span> </span><span class="token" style="color:#ce9178">&quot;null&quot;</span><span>
</span><span> </span><span class="token" style="color:#d4d4d4">}</span><span>
</span><span> </span><span class="token" style="color:#d4d4d4">]</span><span>
</span><span> </span><span class="token" style="color:#d4d4d4">}</span><span>

</span><span> </span><span class="token" style="color:#d4d4d4">}</span><span>
</span><span> </span><span class="token" style="color:#d4d4d4">}</span><span class="token" style="color:#d4d4d4">,</span><span>
</span><span> </span><span class="token" style="color:#9cdcfe">&quot;additionalProperties&quot;</span><span class="token" style="color:#d4d4d4">:</span><span> </span><span class="token" style="color:#569cd6">false</span><span class="token" style="color:#d4d4d4">,</span><span>
</span><span> </span><span class="token" style="color:#9cdcfe">&quot;required&quot;</span><span class="token" style="color:#d4d4d4">:</span><span> </span><span class="token" style="color:#d4d4d4">[</span><span class="token" style="color:#ce9178">&quot;file_system&quot;</span><span class="token" style="color:#d4d4d4">]</span><span>
</span><span></span><span class="token" style="color:#d4d4d4">}</span></code></pre></div></div></div>
<h2 id="json-object-mode" class="[&amp;:not(:first-child)]:mt-12 mb-3 text-xl w-fit font-semibold font-header hover:underline"><a href="#json-object-mode" class="anchor-link">JSON Object Mode</a></h2>
<p class="text-sm my-3">JSON Object Mode provides basic JSON output validation without schema enforcement. Unlike Structured Outputs with <code class="bg-gray-100 dark:bg-gray-800 py-0.5 px-[0.5em] rounded-[4px]">json_schema</code> mode, it is designed to output valid JSON syntax but not schema compliance. The endpoint will either return valid JSON or throw an error if the model cannot produce valid JSON syntax. Use <a class="inline-flex items-center gap-1 transition-colors duration-200 font-inter text-foreground underline underline-offset-2 hover:text-primaryaccent text-sm" href="#introduction">Structured Outputs</a> when available for your use case.</p>
<br/>
<p class="text-sm my-3">Enable JSON Object Mode by setting <code class="bg-gray-100 dark:bg-gray-800 py-0.5 px-[0.5em] rounded-[4px]">response_format</code> to <code class="bg-gray-100 dark:bg-gray-800 py-0.5 px-[0.5em] rounded-[4px]">{ &quot;type&quot;: &quot;json_object&quot; }</code>.</p>
<br/>
<p class="text-sm my-3"><strong>Requirements and limitations:</strong></p>
<ul class="list-disc my-1 text-sm">
<li class="ml-6 my-1.5 text-sm">Include explicit JSON instructions in your prompt (system message or user input)</li>
<li class="ml-6 my-1.5 text-sm">Outputs are syntactically valid JSON but may not match your intended schema</li>
<li class="ml-6 my-1.5 text-sm">Combine with validation libraries and retry logic for schema compliance</li>
</ul>
<h3 id="sentiment-analysis-example" class="mt-8 mb-3 text-base w-fit font-semibold font-header hover:underline"><a href="#sentiment-analysis-example" class="anchor-link">Sentiment Analysis Example</a></h3>

def main():

messages=[
{
&quot;role&quot;: &quot;system&quot;,
&quot;content&quot;: &quot;&quot;&quot;You are a data analysis API that performs sentiment analysis on text.
Respond only with JSON using this format:
{
&quot;sentiment_analysis&quot;: {
&quot;sentiment&quot;: &quot;positive|negative|neutral&quot;,

}
}&quot;&quot;&quot;

}
],
response_format={&quot;type&quot;: &quot;json_object&quot;}
)

result = json.loads(response.choices[0].message.content)
print(json.dumps(result, indent=2))

if __name__ == &quot;__main__&quot;:

<p class="text-sm my-3">System prompts structure the output format while maintaining JSON validity. However, keep in mind that the JSON object output may not match your schema.</p>

</span><span> </span><span class="token" style="color:#9cdcfe">&quot;phrase&quot;</span><span class="token" style="color:#d4d4d4">:</span><span> </span><span class="token" style="color:#ce9178">&quot;absolutely love this product&quot;</span><span class="token" style="color:#d4d4d4">,</span><span>
</span><span> </span><span class="token" style="color:#9cdcfe">&quot;sentiment&quot;</span><span class="token" style="color:#d4d4d4">:</span><span> </span><span class="token" style="color:#ce9178">&quot;positive&quot;</span><span>
</span><span> </span><span class="token" style="color:#d4d4d4">}</span><span class="token" style="color:#d4d4d4">,</span><span>
</span><span> </span><span class="token" style="color:#d4d4d4">{</span><span>
</span><span> </span><span class="token" style="color:#9cdcfe">&quot;phrase&quot;</span><span class="token" style="color:#d4d4d4">:</span><span> </span><span class="token" style="color:#ce9178">&quot;quality exceeded my expectations&quot;</span><span class="token" style="color:#d4d4d4">,</span><span>
</span><span> </span><span class="token" style="color:#9cdcfe">&quot;sentiment&quot;</span><span class="token" style="color:#d4d4d4">:</span><span> </span><span class="token" style="color:#ce9178">&quot;positive&quot;</span><span>
</span><span> </span><span class="token" style="color:#d4d4d4">}</span><span>
</span><span> </span><span class="token" style="color:#d4d4d4">]</span><span class="token" style="color:#d4d4d4">,</span><span>
</span><span> </span><span class="token" style="color:#9cdcfe">&quot;summary&quot;</span><span class="token" style="color:#d4d4d4">:</span><span> </span><span class="token" style="color:#ce9178">&quot;The reviewer loves the product&#x27;s quality, but was slightly disappointed with the shipping time.&quot;</span><span>
</span><span> </span><span class="token" style="color:#d4d4d4">}</span><span>
</span><span></span><span class="token" style="color:#d4d4d4">}</span></code></pre></div></div></div></div></details>
<br/>
<p class="text-sm my-3"><strong>Response structure:</strong></p>
<ul class="list-disc my-1 text-sm">
<li class="ml-6 my-1.5 text-sm"><strong>sentiment</strong>: Classification (positive/negative/neutral)</li>
<li class="ml-6 my-1.5 text-sm"><strong>confidence_score</strong>: Confidence level (0-1 scale)</li>
<li class="ml-6 my-1.5 text-sm"><strong>key_phrases</strong>: Extracted phrases with individual sentiment scores</li>
<li class="ml-6 my-1.5 text-sm"><strong>summary</strong>: Analysis overview and main findings</li>
